## Part 8: Implementation Comparison

### Transaction Economics

**Current Structure (Polaris 2025-3 baseline):**

```
Weighted Average Coupon (WAC):
Class A (87.75%): SONIA + 0.82% → 0.72% weighted
Class B (5.50%):  SONIA + 1.10% → 0.06% weighted
Class C (3.25%):  SONIA + 1.40% → 0.05% weighted
Class D (1.75%):  SONIA + 1.65% → 0.03% weighted
Class E (0.75%):  SONIA + 2.48% → 0.02% weighted
Class F (0.80%):  SONIA + 3.98% → 0.03% weighted
Class G (0.20%):  SONIA + 5.48% → 0.01% weighted
Class X1 (2.50%): SONIA + 3.59% → 0.09% weighted
Class X2 (1.50%): SONIA + 3.59% → 0.05% weighted

Total WAC (all tranches): SONIA + 1.06%
Annual funding cost (at 4% SONIA): £22.6M
```

**Proposed Structure:**

```
Weighted Average Coupon (WAC):
Class A (88.50%): SONIA + 0.77% → 0.68% weighted  (5 bps tighter)
Class B (5.25%):  SONIA + 1.05% → 0.06% weighted  (5 bps tighter)
Class C (3.00%):  SONIA + 1.30% → 0.04% weighted  (10 bps tighter for upgrade)
Class D (1.75%):  SONIA + 1.50% → 0.03% weighted  (15 bps tighter for upgrade)
Class E (1.50%):  ZERO            → 0.00% weighted  ✓

Total WAC (all tranches): SONIA + 0.81%
Annual funding cost (at 4% SONIA): £21.2M

Annual Savings: £1.4M
NPV Savings (7-year WAL): £8.5M
```

### Execution Timeline Comparison

|Phase             |Current Structure                                                                    |Proposed Structure                                            |Time Saved    |
|------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|--------------|
|**Rating Process**|3 separate X notes<br>Complex F/G/X waterfall analysis<br>Multiple deferral scenarios|Single E note<br>Simple waterfall<br>Standard BB deferral     |**-1 week**   |
|**Marketing**     |5 different junior buyers<br>Complex story for each<br>F/G hard to place             |1-2 junior buyers<br>Single equity story<br>Clean BB placement|**-2 weeks**  |
|**Documentation** |5 PDL accounts<br>Complex turbo mechanics<br>Multiple step-up provisions             |1 PDL account<br>Simple turbo<br>Single step-up               |**-1 week**   |
|**Total**         |~10-12 weeks                                                                         |~6-8 weeks                                                    |**-4 weeks** ✓|

