## Part 9: Final Recommendations

### Optimal Structure for New Polaris

**Recommended Capital Structure:**

```
Class A:     £389.4M  (88.50%)  CE: 11.50%  AAA (sf)  SONIA+0.75-0.80%
Class B-Dfrd: £23.1M  (5.25%)   CE: 6.25%   AA (sf)   SONIA+1.05-1.10%
Class C-Dfrd: £13.2M  (3.00%)   CE: 3.25%   A (sf)    SONIA+1.30-1.40%
Class D-Dfrd: £7.7M   (1.75%)   CE: 1.50%   BBB+ (sf) SONIA+1.50-1.65%
Class E-Dfrd: £6.6M   (1.50%)   CE: 0.00%   BB (sf)   Zero Coupon

Total: £440M
```

**Key Features:**

```
✓ 44% fewer tranches (5 vs. 9)
✓ 75 bps lower AAA CE (11.50% vs. 12.25%)
✓ 25 bps lower aggregate WAC (SONIA+0.81% vs. +1.06%)
✓ £1.4M annual funding savings
✓ Zero coupon E-Dfrd eliminates excess spread drag
✓ Cleaner execution (4 weeks faster)
✓ Better distribution (single BB equity story)
✓ Two rating upgrades (C: A- → A, D: BBB- → BBB+)
```

